The cyan hap (Pseudotropheus cyaneus) is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from Chinyamwezi Island.  It prefers areas with plentiful rocks down to a depth of approximately 40 metres (130 ft) where it can graze from the rocks.  This species can reach a length of 7.8 centimetres (3.1 in) SL.  It can also be found in the aquarium trade.